15:39.119 --> 15:40.520
they had a three-day rodeo. So we'd book in for 
three nights of dance. And, uh, I don't know. It was

15:46.569 --> 15:47.250
very familiar. West Texas dance. There's not 
anything out now that I can pull up, you know. About

15:52.978 --> 15:54.520
how many were in his band? There was nine of us, I 
believe, in that band, in Buzz's band. And, uh...

16:00.235 --> 16:01.196
What did they play? What instruments? We probably 
had three saxes, two or three trumpets, two

16:02.939 --> 16:12.673
trombones, bass, piano, and drummer. And what 
kind of music did you all play? We played, I guess,

16:16.038 --> 16:24.330
the big band stuff. Do you remember how much pay you 
got? Yeah, it was very little, about $5 an hour,

16:29.075 --> 16:32.840
something like that. But that was pretty good pay, 
though, for that era. Yeah. How did y'all travel?

16:38.146 --> 16:41.069
The band leader owned the bus, and he drove it. 
Although, finally, the bass man, yeah, the bass

16:41.910 --> 16:49.259
man finally did the driving, you know, and they 
swapped off. And one night, the bass man went down

16:50.380 --> 16:54.886
in South Africa. We didn't play in a place. And we'd 
move over to the next town where we'd go and check in

16:56.969 --> 17:02.440
the motel about daylight. And then we'd stay there 
all day, and then we'd see it at night. So it kind of

17:07.510 --> 17:10.776
helped us out. So our extension was used up. But the 
base man, he was down about two or three o'clock in

17:13.575 --> 17:25.707
the morning. And he had some kind of stomach 
problem. It required emergency treatment. And

17:29.110 --> 17:31.873
they went to the hospital. So we put him in the 
hospital. And I think he had to be in there several

17:32.754 --> 17:34.836
days. But anyway, that's just one of the little 
things that you put up with when you're out on the

17:34.856 --> 17:39.480
road. Did y'all go out of state, or did you stay in 
Texas? We stayed in Texas with that band. I had gone

17:47.564 --> 17:53.854
to Durango, Colorado

17:47.564 --> 17:53.854
with that band. A member of it, in that band, wanted 
me to come to Texas. We stayed in Durango for about a

18:00.463 --> 18:06.312
year, and then we came back to Texas.

